on="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="0"/></CodeI></Code><Code value="asiaz"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Asia</CodeD><CodeI org="expansion" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="root" value="re:singp"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="0"/></CodeI></Code><Code value="seasiaz"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Southeast Asia</CodeD><CodeI org="expansion" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="root" value="re:singp"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="1"/></CodeI></Code></CSet><CSet fid="ns"><Code value="gcat"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Political/General News</CodeD><CodeI org="rbc" action="add"><CodeA name="rule" value="805588"/><CodeA name="db" value="prbc---00018569-20180321-145544"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="0"/></CodeI></Code></CSet></CodeSets><DescTPC fid="de"><DescField fid="ipd">Cycling Environment </DescField></DescTPC></MetadataPT><ArchiveDoc xml:space="preserve"><Article markup="pp0" lang="en" index="field"><HandL fid="hlp"><Title fid="hl"><SectionName fid="se" index="field">Voices</SectionName><ColumnName fid="clm" index="field"></ColumnName><Headline fid="hd"><Para lang="en">Penalties should be imposed for littering of shared bikes </Para></Headline></Title><LeadPara fid="lp"><Para>Under the amendments made to the Parking Places Act in Parliament on March 20, users caught parking shared bikes indiscriminately more than three times a year will be temporarily banned from renting from any bike-sharing operators (“Shared-bike users caught parking indiscriminately more than 3 times a year will face collective ban”; March 20).</Para><Para>This is a good move but more can be done.</Para></LeadPara></HandL><TailParas fid="td"><Para>I am a cyclist and, on my regular trips, I have seen shared bikes that were abandoned by users. On Wednesday (March 21) morning, I saw the worst case of abuse that I have personally come across. It was dumped into Sungai Changi, near the Changi Point Ferry Terminal. It was low tide and the bike could be seen near the bank. It would have been submerged otherwise.</Para><Para>It was likely tossed into the river by a user or someone else. Not only is littering an offence, but are our rivers and waterways becoming a dumping ground for bicycles?</Para><Para>Last month, Member of Parliament Lim Biow Chuan raised the issue of imposing fines on cyclists who throw shared bicycles on the roadside and users who park indiscriminately. We should indeed look into such penalties for littering and vandalising of property, too.</Para></TailParas><Byline fid="by" index="field">Tay Yong Hong </Byline><Credit fid="cr" index="field"></Credit><Contact fid="ct" index="field"></Contact><Notes fid="rf" index="field"></Notes><Art fid="art" index="field"></Art><Copyright fid="cy" index="field">(c) 2018. MediaCorp Press Ltd. </Copyright></Article></ArchiveDoc><AdocTOC adoctype="article"><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/ArchiveDoc::Article" type="arttext"></Item><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/InvertText" type="invtext"></Item></AdocTOC></DistDoc>

